Carpetright Profit Drops 90% in First Half, Mail on Sunday Says

-- B y   G a v i n   F i n c h
-- 
2011-12-11T15:51:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-11/carpetright-profit-drops-90-in-first-half-mail-on-sunday-says.html
Carpetright Plc (CPR)  will say this week
that profit tumbled by 90 percent in the fiscal first half
through October, the Mail on Sunday reported, without saying
where it got the information.  Profit during the period dropped to about 1 million pounds
($1.6 million), the worst performance since the company listed
on the London Stock Exchange in 1993, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gavin Finch in London at 
 gfinch@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at   eevans3@bloomberg.net  